    new ""

    # game/areas/rockslide.rpy:627
    old "The undead didn’t even have its hips, and it was lucky to “sit” in an upward position. “Was this wretch buried by the tree, or did it get trapped after it died here,” wonders one of the guards, and a digger responds by spitting on the ground. “Let’s hope nae one was stupid enough to ne burn their dead.” \n\nThe hesitant workers try to stay away from the bones, but then {color=#f6d6bd}the overseer{/color} kicks the skull away, sparking another wave of laughter. He cups his head around his mouth. “Now, now! There may be another one here, en its legs may still be kicking! Grab your tools, we do ne have more than an hour ahead of us!” \n\nHe turns toward you and nods politely. “You know how to get rid of a corpse on the road. What do we do?” "
